title: Millie Bobby Brown From ‘Stranger Things’ Was The Cutest Star At The SAG Awards
text:
Like Us On Facebook Like Us On Facebook 
Millie Bobby Brown, one of the many breakout stars of Netflix’s “ Stranger Things ,” already has more grace and elegance in her pinky finger at 12 years old than I do in my entire body. 
I ain’t even mad because look how adorable she looks in her red Emporio Armani gown. REX/Shutterstock 
The actress rocked the sleeveless, belted, red gown, which the designer sketched for her himself, ensuring she looked totally unique on the red carpet. 
Brown is nominated for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Drama Series for her work on “Stranger Thing,” where she plays Eleven, a girl with psychokinetic powers and a love of waffles. 
The category also boasts her co-star Winona Ryder, Claire Foy (“The Crown”), Thandie Newton (“Westworld”) and Robin Wright (“House of Cards”). REX/Shutterstock 
It’s cool if I make someone 15 years younger than me my style icon, right? Because yo’ girl just ordered three dozen different headbands off Amazon and I think this is going to be my year, guys. 
So you can tell the truth. 
Yes, or HECK YES, those headbands will look adorable on me? 
The young actress is set to star in her first Hollywood blockbuster , the highly anticipated “Godzilla” sequel, “Godzilla: King of Monsters.” 
Brown’s character and the movie’s storyline are still a secret, so fans will have to wait until closer to the 2019 release of the movie to find out more. REX/Shutterstock 
Millie Bobby Brown and her co-stars will return to “Stranger Things” later this year. The show will pick up in 1984, right where it left off. 
Yes, that probably does mean you’ll have to watch Will Byers (Noah Schnapp) throw up a slug again. 
It is also expected that the second season holds a “bigger mythology” behind Will’s disappearance. 
There will certainly be a lot more mystery to come. 
Also a mystery? How did Millie Bobby Brown and the other kids of “Stranger Things” get so much swag ?
